right now I use hey.com for adding a layer of security against phishing attacks, I have been receiving a couple very good attempts pretending to be coinbase ...

... what hey.com does is it needs me to approve a DNS record, so if I approve coinbase.com once, it just auto adds them to my inbox, but if there is a shady scammer trying to phish using a similar looking domain, then I need to re-approve this new domain.
